Most philosophers who find Kant’s views attractive find them so because
of the Humanity Formulation of the CI. This formulation states that we
should never act in such a way that we treat humanity, whether in
ourselves or in others, as a means only but always as an end in itself.
This is often seen as introducing the idea of “respect” for persons,
that is, respect for whatever it is that is essential to our humanity.

SOURCE: Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy
